This model is identical to the Lorenz demo, except that it uses a DifferentialSystem actor rather than discrete components to build up the dynamical system. Also, this has an input port.
It shows a nonlinear feedback system that exhibits chaotic behavior. It is modeled in continuous time. The Continuous director uses a sophisticated ordinary differential equation solver to execute the model. This particular model is known as a Lorenz attractor.
